StatCrunch Chapter 3

Comparing Albert Pujols and Manny Rameriz

To illustrate the construction of graphs in comparison, we use the Pujols/Rameriz season-to-season batting data contained in the data file TSUB case 3.1.

Comparing OPS Values by Dotplots

Suppose I want to construct parallel dotplots for the OPS values for the two players.

I open up the Graph menu:

If I select the Dotplot option, I see the following window. I select the variable OPS, let the grouping variable by Player, and then select Calculate.

I see parallel dotplots.

One can add the Median to each plot in the Dotplot box, choose the Marker median.

Comparing OPS Values by Boxplots

First choose Graphs -> Boxplots from the main menu. In the dialog box, select column OPS and Group by Player.

Summaries

To find summary stats for each player

Choose the Stat > Summary Stats menu item. Select the Columns option.

Select the column OPS and Group by Player.

You get an assortment of different summary statistics for each player.
